related_questions.title: AI Overview
list: Non-uniform composition: The key characteristic of a heterogeneous mixture is that its composition varies throughout. Different samples taken from the mixture will have different amounts of the various components.
Visible components: You can see the different substances or phases (solid, liquid, gas) within the mixture with the naked eye or with a simple magnifying glass.
Separate phases: Heterogeneous mixtures often have two or more distinct phases, meaning you can clearly see where one substance ends and another begins.
Examples: Common examples include a bowl of salad, a handful of trail mix, or a glass of muddy water. In these examples, you can easily see the different ingredients or particles within the mixture.
Separation: Heterogeneous mixtures can often be separated into their original components using simple physical methods like filtering or sorting.

text_blocks.snippet: A heterogeneous mixture is a type of mixture where the components are not evenly distributed and their individual substances can be visually distinguished. Examples include trail mix, pizza, concrete, chocolate chip cookies, and sand in water.
snippet_highlighted_words: trail mix, pizza, concrete, chocolate chip cookies, and sand in water

list.title: Non-uniform composition:
list.snippet: In a heterogeneous mixture, the composition varies throughout the mixture. You can observe different parts with different properties.

list.title: Visually distinguishable components:
list.snippet: Unlike homogeneous mixtures where components blend seamlessly, in heterogeneous mixtures, you can typically see the individual components.
Trail mix: Different nuts, seeds, and dried fruits are easily identified.
Pizza: Cheese, sauce, crust, and toppings are distinct and not evenly spread.
Concrete: A mixture of cement, sand, and gravel with visible aggregate particles.
Chocolate chip cookies: The dough and chocolate chips are easily differentiated.
Sand in water: Sand settles to the bottom and is clearly separate from the water.
Vegetable soup: Different vegetables and other ingredients are present and easily identified.

list.title: Other examples:
list.snippet: Mixed nuts, salad, a bowl of colorful candies, and even blood can be considered heterogeneous mixtures.
